      • createDeviceProfile

        public PushDeviceSettings createDeviceProfile()
        Creates and saves a fresh device profile for the given user. This will generate a fresh random shared secret for the device, ensuring a valid device profile is present for device registration.
        Returns:
        the generated device profile.

                              String realm,

                       throws AuthLoginException
        Saves the Push device settings to the user's profile, overwriting any existing device profile.
        Parameters:
        user - the username of the user to generate a device profile for. Cannot be null.
        realm - the realm of the user. Cannot be null.
        deviceSettings - the device profile to save. Cannot be null.
        Throws:
        AuthLoginException - if the device profile cannot be saved.
